      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The view "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Invoice.vwInvoiceAmounts",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to aggregate financial data related to invoices from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Invoice.InvoiceAccountBilling",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. It provides a summarized view of the total amounts billed and paid for each invoice, identified by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "InvoiceID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The use of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ISNULL",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " ensures that even if there are no amounts billed or paid, the view will return a default value of 0.00 for those fields. This view is useful for reporting and analysis purposes, allowing users to quickly assess the financial status of invoices."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this view is considered low. It involves a straightforward aggregation operation using "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SUM",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and a "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "GROUP BY",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " clause. The view references a single table and does not involve any joins, subqueries, or complex logic. The use of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ISNULL",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a simple mechanism to handle potential null values."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
